  "prompt": "While having sex, I got a cut on my penis and it started bleeding heavily. I went to the doctor and he stitched it. Right now the penis is swollen and he said circumcision is the best option. Is it normal to face this issue? Shall I go for circumcision or not?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about your injury. Here are some general suggestions:\n\n1. Follow your doctor's medical advice closely, as they have examined you directly.\n\n2. Circumcision might be recommended if:\n- The wound is severe\n- There's high risk of infection\n- Healing is complicated\n- Repeated injuries or complications occur\n\n3. Consider getting a second medical opinion from another urologist\n\n4. Discuss potential risks and benefits of circumcision with your doctor\n\n5. Important medical details to clarify with your doctor:\n- Exact nature of the injury\n- Severity of the wound\n- Healing potential\n- Long-term implications\n\n6. Ask about alternative treatment options\n\n7. Understand potential post-surgical care and recovery\n\nRemember, this is a personal medical decision best discussed thoroughly with professional medical experts who can assess your specific situation.",
